definition.value: A glycosyloxyflavone that is kaempferol substituted by a 2-O-beta-D-glucopyranosyl-beta-D-galactopyranosyl residue at position 3 via a glycosidic linkage.
A  C-glycosyl compound that is (S)-naringenin substituted by a beta-D-glucopyranosyl residue at position 8 via a C-glycosidic linkage.
A member of the juvenile hormone family of compounds that is the methyl ester of farnesoic acid. Found in several species of crustaceans.
A member of the juvenile hormone family of compounds obtained by formal hydrolysis of the methyl ester group of juvenile hormone III.
A desulfoglucosinolic acid resulting from the formal condensation of the thiol group of N-hydroxy(indol-3-yl)ethanethioamide with beta-D-glucopyranose.
